channel.title: One Woman Server...Nobody can get on!
channel.description:
Hello there. Other topic got locked.. :mad: Anyways... I portforwarded with my server, updated the no-ip with the DUC, and tried to log on with the no-ip name. I can't get on.. Only way to get on is if I use "localhost"
I use a Speedstream router. When I portforwarded I allowed the Protocol TCP, Port 43594, then I redirected to my IP. When I did no-ip and it asks for your IP when you're making a new host, I put in the same IP I did when I did for portforwarding instead of keeping the one they had already filled in. Any help please :)
